be.pxl.poker

Enum PokerHand.ValueType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<PokerHand.ValueType>
      • be.pxl.poker.PokerHand.ValueType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<PokerHand.ValueType>
    Enclosing class:
    PokerHand

    public static enum PokerHand.ValueType
extends java.lang.Enum<PokerHand.ValueType>

    Representation of the hand ranking (conform hand ranking hierarchy of the standard(straight) 5 card poker game).

    Containing:
    • A description which is the standard name for the ranking used in a poker game.
    • A minimum value which can be used to represent the hand ranking as an integer.
    Individual elements:
    • ROYAL_FLUSH
    • STRAIGHT_FLUSH
    • FOUR_OF_A_KIND
    • FULL_HOUSE
    • FLUSH
    • STRAIGHT
    • THREE_OF_A_KIND
    • TWO_PAIR
    • ONE_PAIR
    • HIGH_CARD
